			<td class="content"><h1 class="static_h1">What is Landlord Terminal</h1>
Landlord Terminal <!--is a Cloud-based hotel booking/property management system. The application and data is hosted on our server, so you don’t need to install any complex software or buy any expensive computers or set up a network.  With only an internet connection and a PC or Mac computer you can manage your customer’s reservations, checkins, checkouts and repairs.-->helps you manage bookings, guests, payments and tasks. Increase occupancy rate by connecting your hotel to major internet booking engines. Convert your website visitors into guests by embedding an online booking module. Organize your own multi-property booking engine in your design, on your domain.

	<h1 class="static_h1">What it includes</h1>

<strong class="static_highlight">Online Booking Engines</strong> – increase your direct bookings by installing our real-time online booking module literally within minutes. You only have to configure the appearance of the hotel/apartment description, services, facilities, rates, and the forms presentation via the user-friendly administration interface, to receive a small piece of embed code and put it at one of your website pages. In case if you manage multiple properties we could offer our comprehensive <a href="/en/multi_property_booking_engine">Multi-Property Online Booking Engine</a>.

	<br />
	<br />

<strong class="static_highlight">Channel Management</strong> – boost your occupancy rate and reduce the time and cost it takes to update availability and rates manually. With Landlord Terminal you can now manage all of your online distribution from a single cloud application. Landlord Terminal has direct 2-way connect to world’s leading booking websites: Booking.com, Expedia (Including Venere, Hotels.com and Hotwire), Agoda, Lastminute/Travelocity, Orbitz, Hotelbeds, Airbnb, Wimdu and TripAdvisor. Other <a href="/en/faq_ids_gds/#1">booking sites</a> and online travel agencies could be connected via our channel management partners AvailPro, BBLiveRate or Cultuzz.
	<br />
	<br />
<strong class="static_highlight">Reporting System</strong> – get a clear vision of how your properties are performing. In Landlord Terminal you can setup as many reports as you need and schedule when each report will be automatically generated and where it should be delivered. You determine what fields should be shown, in what order and how the fields can be filtered.
	<br />
	<br />
	<strong class="static_highlight">Frontdesk</strong> – Landlord Terminal's Reservation Board is laid out as a grid that displays a real-time status of your property. You can create or update bookings on it directly and all your users will immediately see these changes on their Reservation Boards or Dashboards. A powerful filtering system helps you quickly hide all un-relevant information from your screen.
	<br />
	<br />
	<strong class="static_highlight">Dashboard</strong> – gives your users quick access to most useful information on one screen. Dashboard displays following information: new reservations, upcoming check-ins and check-outs, currently available rooms, most urgent tasks and its current status. When you or any one of your users updates information, the change is immediately displayed to all other your users in real-time on dashboard. 
	<br />
	<br />
	<strong class="static_highlight">Task Management System</strong> – sends current information about the existing repair tasks and other issues to the relevant users in real time. Landlord Terminal has a flexible system of statuses, priorities and reports so you can customize the system's workflow to fit you internal work processes. The notification system and integration with Dashboard guarantees that the appropriate employee will receive assigned tasks in time.
	<br />
	<br />
